g.text: Imagine a nice evening at home in the wintertime.
Outside cold and dark, inside cozy and light. Lamps and
luminaires are an important and emotional part of
your home. However, even if they are already much more
efficient, they consume energy. Especially when the entire
house is illuminated even if certain rooms are empty.
Occupation-based lighting can avoid this and help to save
significant amounts of energy: Radar sensors use
presence detection to make sure that lights are only on
when a person is in the room.
XENSIV 60 GHz radar sensors can help reduce the energy
consumption of lighting modules. An estimated saving of
only 5% corresponds to an energy quantity of more than
2 TWh or almost 1 million tons of CO

text.tspan: Smart lighting with XENSIV 60 GHz radar sensor
